<TITLE> Moudud out on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 1 (bdnews24.com)Former law minister Moudud Ahmed was released on bail Monday evening, said a top prison official. The BNP leader was released from guard at the prison wing of BSMMU Hospital at around 5.30pm, deputy inspector general of prisons Maj Shamsul haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com. After securing bail on Nov 26 in the Niko graft case, his counsel Barrister Mahbubuddin Khokon had said Moudud had no more legal barriers to being released as he had earlier been granted bail in the five other cases against him. The ex-minister was arrested on Apr. 13 last year from his Gulshan residence. bdn
